Were said Odera has been one of the paramount forces behind the steady rise of Wazalendo club and it will only be fair for the club to stand with him at his time of need."Wazalendo has been assisting to supplement his upkeep in the village. And now that he is going for the second surgery, we are trying in our own little ways, but we are also reaching out to the whole nation to help us have a successful initiative. As a club, we still need Odera's services and we hope to raise the amount so that the surgery can be conducted for Odera to resume his normal life," said the official. Former international hockey player Julius Odera is in dire need of financial help to undergo a brain tumor surgery.
Odera, who was attached to Kenya Breweries team, played for the national team from 1986 to 1993 before he called it quits.
The former Kenya Railway employee is partially blind and needs Sh750,000 to undergo an operation at Moi Teaching and Referral Hospital, Eldoret.



