When contacted on Sunday, Odera, 59, whose speech is also slur, hopes people will hear his cry and come to his aid.
His wife, Cindy Morphine, said life has never been the same since her husband's first operation in 2004.
Odera underwent an Epileptic surgery at Kenyatta Hospital in 2004.
"Wazalendo club has been taking care of us since then and the Railways pension income has not been reliable. The situation forced us to move to Kisumu in 2009.Â  I'm aware my husband (Odera) played for Kenya won a couple of events. I hope that with those memories, well wishers and people of good will help us raise the amount," said Morphine.



