Wazalendo secretary general James Were said they will conduct a virtual fund raising on Tuesday.
Were said Odera has been one of the paramount forces behind the steady rise of Wazalendo club and it will only be fair for the club to stand with him at his time of need.
"Wazalendo has been assisting to supplement his upkeep in the village. And now that he is going for the second surgery, we are trying in our own little ways, but we are also reaching out to the whole nation to help us have a successful initiative. As a club, we still need Odera's services and we hope to raise the amount so that the surgery can be conducted for Odera to resume his normal life," said the official.



